gurmukhi: sjy ssqR pwxM ] cVy jMg juAwxM ]33]189]
transliteration: Saje Sastra Paanan|| Chade Jan Juaanan||33||189||
translation: His soldiers bedecked with weapons came forward to wage war.33.189.
The sound created by drums, bows;
The swords of the persistent and renowned fighters glistened.

gurmukhi: mhw bIr huMky ] su nIswx dRMuky ]35]191]
transliteration: Mahaa Boor Hounke|| Su Noosaan Drounke||35||191||
translation: The great heroes raised loud shouts and the trumpets sounded.35.191.

gurmukhi: chUM Er grjy ] sbY dyv lrjy ]
transliteration: Chahoon Or Gadje|| Sabai Dev Larje||
translation: The demons thundered from all the four sides and the gods collectively trembled.

gurmukhi: srM Dwr brKy ] meIXw pwx prKy ]36]192]
transliteration: Saran Dhaar Barkhe|| Maooyaa Paan Parkhe||36||192||
translation: Showering her arrows Durga herself is testing the dtength of all.36.192.

gurmukhi: jy ley ssqR swmuhy Dey ] iqqy inDn khuM pRwpiq Bey ]
transliteration: Je Lae Sastra Saamuhe Dhae|| Tite Nidhan Kahoun Praapat(i) Bhae||
translation: All those demons, carrying their weapons, came in front of the goddess were all subjected to death.

gurmukhi: Jmkq BeI Asn kI Dwrw ] BBky ruMf muMf ibkrwrw ]37]193]
transliteration: Jhamkat Bhaoo Asan Koo Dhaaraa|| Bhabbke Round Mounnd Bikaaraa||37||193||
translation: The edges of the swords are glistening and the headless trunks, in dreadful forms are raising their voices.37.193.

gurmukhi: hY gY rQ pYdl kty bicE n jIvq koie ]
transliteration: Hai Gad Rath Paidal Kate Bachio Na Jeev at Koe||
translation: The elephants, horses and warriors on foot were all chopped and none could survive.

gurmukhi: qb Awpy inksXo niRpiq suMB krY so hoie ]38]194]
transliteration: Tah Aape Niksayo Nripat(i) Sounbh Darai So Hoe||38||194||
translation: Then the king Sumbh himself marched forward for war and on seeing him it appears that whatever he desires, he will achive.38.194.
